   <mods:abstract>Encloses three parcels of bills whose owners expect they will be accepted
            by tomorrow night's post. Two bills of 333 and one of 444 are due tomorrow. Gardoqui has
            promised to deliver the paper to answer these and other drafts due next month. Suggest
            that if Gardoqui has done so, Jay should place it in the hands of the same person to
            whom Jay directed that Carmichael give the cash. Dining with Cabarrus. Asks for orders
            by the bearer. A note on the second page in Jay's hand and of the same date asks that
            Carmichael receive the notes from Gardoqui mentioned in his note and place them in the
            hands of the same banker to whom he gave the other money,</mods:abstract>
